Binary Trees are proper/full if each node has either zero or two children
Used for recurring Y/N decisions (decision trees)
Level - The set of all nodes of a binary tree T at the same depth d as level d of T
In general: Level d has max 2^d nodes
Types: Proper, Complete, Perfect, Degenerate (right/left skewed)
Implementation (linked-nodes structure and array structure)

